It doesn't crash, and keeps handling queries, but it stops reporting block updates, and fails to self post its weights, leading to the update number climbing. It took me a while of reading code to find this out, so sharing with the rest of the miners here, in case they're having issues like I was with understanding if they're at risk of deregistration.  Currently, with burn based registration, if someone is willing to pay the burn fee / registration cost (as shown here https://taostats.io/subnets/netuid-3/#registration), someone *will* get kicked off the subnet.  And up to three miners can be kicked off in each period of 360 blocks.

The subtensor picks which nodes get kicked off by looking at the prune score, which is basically your emission, which is based on your incentive, the distribution of which is displayed nicely here, now: https://taostats.io/subnets/netuid-3/#distribution
Essentially if your miner's incentive is one of the lowest three on that chart, and you're out of the immunity period (5000 blocks since registration), your miner is at risk of deregistration.
It's not directly based on rank, as I first assumed.
It’s based on emission
yep, and emission is just incentive normalized along with validator dividends, so if you're just looking at incentive, like that graph does, the lowest three positions there are the ones "at risk".
it's actually just the lowest one, and if tie, it's reverse sorted by uid to determine deregistration
Yeah, but there can be three registrations each period, and when the registration cost dips, typically all three are used within the first few blocks.
